AGI - There was a reason why Kate, the Princess of Wales, for weeks has disappeared from the public scene; and this reason has a name, indeed three, that of his children: George, Charlotte and Louis. The princess wanted to protect and protect at most the three kids, the biggest of which is just 10 years old, the smallest just five: to publicly explain the situation, he shot a video with which he announced he had a cancer and so he placated the turn of voices, illations and conjectures flourished around his absence, a crisis that the Palace had not been able to placate. The video was released yesterday in the evening and filmed Friday afternoon, immediately after the return to the home of the three children who now begin the Easter holidays. Kate told the world that she has a tumor but told her children first, that they will now stay at home for several weeks, until 17 April, and therefore they will be protected from indiscrete questions. Children speak, sometimes in their innocence are impudent and unconscious: Kate and William will hold them for the next few weeks so that they will be prepared to return to school.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
In the video, which lasts 2 minutes and 15 seconds, Kate sits on a wooden bench with a narcisi flowerbed in the background: it appears determined and cold, sometimes smiling, with bright loose hair, perhaps a little less thick. The princess did not hide the gravity of the situation or the challenge that her illness represents for herself and her family but wanted to send a message of calm. Casual dress with jeans and a striped sweater reviewed the last weeks: "In January I suffered an important abdominal surgery in London and at the time it was thought that my condition was not related to cancer. The surgery was successful. However, examinations after the operation established that there was cancer." He explained that doctors advised her to undergo a treatment of "preventive chemotherapy" which, according to Kensington Palace, began to receive at the end of February.
&nbsp;
"In particular, it took time to explain everything to George, Charlotte and Louis in a way that was appropriate for them, and to reassure them that I will be fine." "As I told them, I am well and stronger every day focusing on the things that will help me heal, in my mind, in my body and in my spirit." King Charles III, also ill of cancer, said himself "very proud" of the daughter's daughter, for "the courage" in talking about cancer that was diagnosed with her. Kate also clarified that she will not participate in official commitments until she is better to focus on her own healing and care of her family. The princess, wife of the heir to the British throne, will not even participate in the religious function on Easter Sunday as she had anticipated the press. As was feared, for the couple it was turbulent and difficult months; but the fact that no one thought to intervene to placate the terrible voices that were circulated confirms that the truth was harder.&nbsp;
